entries.meaning: (fandom slang) A genre of fan fiction in which a character endures injury, torture, or other forms of physical and mental suffering.
examples: By embracing dark genres of slash such as ‘squick’ and ‘whump’, the art of mythagowood purposely skirts parameters of taste and acceptability.

verbs.description: whump (third-person singular simple present whumps, present participle whumping, simple past and past participle whumped)

entries.meaning: (informal, transitive) To strike something with a whump.
